\f6\b \cf0 1. Core Definition\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b0 \cf0 Modularity is the practice of breaking a large application into smaller, self-contained, and manageable pieces (modules). It moves Java from a 
\f6\b Flat Classpath
\f5\b0  (a messy pile of JARs) to an 
\f6\b Organized Module Path
\f5\b0  (labeled boxes with walls).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa331\partightenfactor0

